<page section="download">
  <head><cli-download-refresh release="stable" /></head>
  <heading>Download</heading>

  <content>
    <strong>Downloading <c2 /> <cli /></strong> version <version-stable />...<br />
    <span class="small">If the download does not start automatically, <cli-download-link release="stable">click here</cli-download-link></span>

    <div id="download-info">
      <img src="img/release-3.2.0/cli-batch.png" class="pic" style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;" alt="Carrot2 Command Line Interface Download" />

      <strong>After download completes:</strong>

      <ol>
        <li>
          Extract the archive to some local directory
        </li>

        <li>
          Run <tt>batch.cmd input/</tt> (Windows) <tt>./batch.sh input/</tt> (Linux) to cluster
          all files from the <tt>input/</tt> directory.
        </li>

        <li>
          See <c2 /> Manual for <manual-link target="_blank" section="section.cli.bp.installation">instructions on installation
          and running <c2 /> <cli /></manual-link>.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="note">
        <strong>Note: </strong><c2 /> <cli /> require  <a
        href="http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp"
        target="_blank">Java Runtime Environment</a> (version 1.6.0 or later).
      </p>
    </div>
  </content>
</page>
